<h2 id="200">2. Creating and editing categories</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Have you already thought up a <a href="/en/item/settings/categories#100">meaningful category structure</a>? Then you’re ready to create the main categories and sub-categories that will group your products.</p>
</div>
<ul class="nav nav-tabs mb-3" id="tabCollection" role="tablist"><li class="nav-item">
                                <a class="nav-link active" id="manual-procedure-tab" data-toggle="tab" href="#manual-procedure" role="tab" aria-controls="manual-procedure" aria-selected="true">Manual procedure</a>
                            </li><li class="nav-item">
                                <a class="nav-link" id="data-import-tab" data-toggle="tab" href="#data-import" role="tab" aria-controls="data-import" aria-selected="false">Data import</a>
                            </li><li class="nav-item">
                                <a class="nav-link" id="plentyshop-and-shopbuilder-tab" data-toggle="tab" href="#plentyshop-and-shopbuilder" role="tab" aria-controls="plentyshop-and-shopbuilder" aria-selected="false">plentyShop and ShopBuilder</a>
                            </li></ul><div class="tab-content" id="tabContent"><div class="tab-pane fade show active" id="manual-procedure" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="manual-procedure-tab">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>If you only want to create or edit <em>a few categories</em>, then it’s probably easiest to do so manually.</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>Item » Category</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on <span class="icon green"><i class="fa fa-plus  "></i></span> <strong>New category</strong> in the bottom left corner.<br>
→ The <strong>Create new category</strong> window opens.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Enter a name for the category.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on <span class="icon green"><i class="psicon-save"></i></span> <strong>Create</strong>.<br>
→ The category is created and opened for editing.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
<div class="admonitionblock tip">
<table>
<tbody><tr>
<td class="icon">
<i class="fa icon-tip" title="Tip"></i>
</td>
<td class="content">
Would you rather create a sub-category?
In the settings window, click on <span class="icon blue"><i class="fa fa-dot-circle-o  "></i></span> <strong>Subcategory</strong> and select the category under which you want your new category to appear. Click on a category’s folder icon (<span class="icon darkGrey"><i class="fa fa-folder  "></i></span>) on the far left. This displays the subcategories within.
</td>
</tr>
</tbody></table>
</div>
<div class="admonitionblock tip">
<table>
<tbody><tr>
<td class="icon">
<i class="fa icon-tip" title="Tip"></i>
</td>
<td class="content">
It’s technically possible to create items and categories at the same time.
In other words, you can create a new category while <a href="/en/item/import-export-create/create/new-item#200">manually creating an item</a>.
This method can save you a lot of time but it might also cause you to lose track of your category structure.
</td>
</tr>
</tbody></table>
</div>
</div><div class="tab-pane fade" id="data-import" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="data-import-tab">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>If you want to create or edit <em>a lot of categories</em>, then it’s probably quickest to import the category data.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>The idea is simple.
Rather than manually saving category information in plentymarkets, you’ll enter the same information into a CSV file and then import this file into your system.</p>
</div>
<div class="ulist">
<ul>
<li>
<p><a href="/en/data/importing-data/elasticsync-best-practices/best-practices-elasticsync-categories">Practical example: Importing new categories</a></p>
</li>
<li>
<p><a href="/en/data/importing-data/sync-types/elasticSync-categories">Directory of matching and mapping fields</a></p>
</li>
</ul>
</div>
<div class="admonitionblock tip">
<table>
<tbody><tr>
<td class="icon">
<i class="fa icon-tip" title="Tip"></i>
</td>
<td class="content">
It’s technically possible to create items and categories at the same time.
In other words, you can create a new category while <a href="/en/data/importing-data/sync-types/elasticSync-item#1150">creating an item</a>.
This method can save you a lot of time but it might also cause you to lose track of your category structure.
</td>
</tr>
</tbody></table>
</div>
</div><div class="tab-pane fade" id="plentyshop-and-shopbuilder" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="plentyshop-and-shopbuilder-tab">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>New plentymarkets systems come equipped with plentyShop LTS and a ShopBuilder tool.
You can use these tools to design an attractive store without having to learn HTML and CSS first.
ShopBuilder helps you create the pages of your website and also the categories.
So if you want to use ShopBuilder to create your plentyShop, then you might also want to <a href="/en/online-store/shop-builder#20">use ShopBuilder to create your categories</a> too.</p>
</div>
</div></div>
